headline.main: NEW-JERSEY.; Introduction of Passaic Water into Jersey City. WATER CELEBRATION.

docs.lead_paragraph: New-York has its Croton--Jersey City, at last, has its Passaic. The inaugurations of both have been made the signal for great rejoicings. In yesterday's TIMES we had barely space to record the fact that there was a great celebration in Jersey City on Tuesday, consequent upon the Introduction of Passaic Water.

docs.lead_paragraph: Yesterday our oldest inhabitant celebrated his two hundred and thirteenth birthday ! So far as he knows, all his children are dead. Of his own generation, he is the only relict ; and of many succeeding generations there is no living representative in the City that we know of.

headline.main: LITERARY.; Foreign Items of Literary and Personal News

docs.lead_paragraph: The London Literary Journals are reviewing BENTLEY'S two volumes of The Life and Correspondence of Charles Lord Metcalfe: edited by J. W. KAYE. METCALFE was born in Calcutta 1785, and rose by degrees to be Provisional Governor-General of India.
